            <article class="module col span_14">
            
                <h1>About</h1>
                <p>
                    I am Ph.D. student in the Computer Science department at the 
                    University of California at Irvine. I have the honor of being a part of the UCI 
                    <a class="link" target="_blank" href="http://www.ssllab.org/trac">Secure Systems and Software Lab</a> where I am advised by 
                    <a class="link" target="_blank" href="http://www.ics.uci.edu/~franz/">Prof. Dr. Michael Franz</a>. 
                </p>
                <p>
                    Prior to UCI, I recieved a BS/MS in Computer Science from the 
                    <a class="link" target="_blank" href="http://www.bsuir.by">Belarusian State University of Informatics & Radioelectronics</a>, Minsk, Belarus, in 2010. I had the opportunity to be advised by Viatcheslav Bakhtizin at the Advanced Software Design Technologies Research Group.
                </p>

            </article><!-- span_14 -->

            <article class="module col span_10">
            
                <h1>Research</h1>
                
                <p> 
                    My primary research interest is secure software systems design and evaluation. I am interested in architectural approaches to building secure software (e.g., virtual machines, trusted computing); software analysis (e.g., static analysis and testing, model checking); language-based approaches to building secure software (e.g., type systems, proof-carrying code); and run-time enforcement of security policies (e.g., dynamic taint analysis).
                </p>
                
            </article><!-- span_10 -->

            <article class="module col span_14">
            
